🚀 Optimized Code Snippets

A. Improved Database Wait (with Timeout)

Don't let the script hang forever if the DB container fails to start.

bash

    wait_for_db() {
      log_info "Waiting for MariaDB..."
      local timeout=30
      while ! docker compose exec -T db mysqladmin ping -h localhost --silent; do
        ((timeout--))
        if [ $timeout -le 0 ]; then
          log_error "MariaDB failed to start within 30 seconds."
          exit 1
        fi
        sleep 2
      done
    }
    

Use code with caution.

B. Robust Backup before Rerun

Change your backup to ensure it doesn't fail if the database doesn't exist yet (fresh install).

bash

    backup_env() {
      local e="$1"
      local backup_dir="$HOME/feesix_backups/$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M)/$e"
      
      # Check if DB exists before dumping
      if docker compose exec -T db mariadb -u root -prootsecret -e "use drupal_$e" 2>/dev/null; then
        mkdir -p "$backup_dir"
        log_info "Snapshotting database for $e..."
        docker compose exec -T db mariadb-dump -u root -prootsecret "drupal_$e" | gzip > "$backup_dir/db.sql.gz"
      fi
    }
    

Use code with caution.

C. The Drupal 11 "Composer First" Logic

Inside `manage_env`, Drupal 11 requires a very specific directory structure.

bash

    install_drupal_logic() {
      # Instead of just mkdir, use Composer to build the skeleton
      if [ ! -f "./docroot/$e/composer.json" ]; then
        log_info "Creating Drupal 11 project for $e..."
        docker compose exec -T php composer create-project drupal/recommended-project:^11 "/var/www/html/$e" --no-interaction
        
        # Symlink config/sync outside of web root for security
        docker compose exec -T php mkdir -p "/var/www/html/$e/config/sync"
      fi
    }
    

